<div class="section-flag">Prevention Roadmap</div>

## $446\,200 in annual chargebacks. 73% is preventable.

Cinderhaven carries **$446\,200** in annual retailer chargebacks. Grouping them by root cause and applying a fixed preventability fraction to each category identifies **$324\,888** — 73% of the total — as addressable through four fixable upstream data conditions. This figure is an assumption-driven estimate (historical loss per archetype × its preventability fraction), not a model prediction.

The scoring workflow names the specific data condition driving each purchase order's risk. This report presents the root-cause breakdown, the ranked prevention roadmap, and the economics of fixing versus disputing.

*This analysis uses Cinderhaven synthetic demonstration data to illustrate a repeatable methodology. The numbers, proportions, and root-cause distribution reflect a realistic CPG brand profile.*

